.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_SDKManager
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The SDK Manager script provides configuration of supported SDKs and manages a list of VRTK_SDKSetup s to use.

methods.name: ManageScriptingDefineSymbols(bool ignoreAutoManageScriptDefines, bool ignoreIsActiveAndEnabled)
methods.summary: Manages (i.e. adds and removes) the scripting define symbols of the for the currently set SDK infos. This method is only available in the editor, so usage of the method needs to be surrounded by #if UNITY_EDITOR and #endif when used in a type that is also compiled for a standalone build.
methods.returns: Whether the ' scripting define symbols were changed.

params.value: Whether to ignore autoManageScriptDefines while deciding to manage.

methods.summary: Removes scripting define symbols used by previous VRTK versions.

methods.name: SetLoadedSDKSetupToPopulateObjectReferences(VRTK_SDKSetup setup)
methods.summary: Sets a given VRTK_SDKSetup as the loaded SDK Setup to be able to use it when populating object references in the SDK Setup. This method should only be called when not playing as it's only for populating the object references. This method is only available in the editor, so usage of the method needs to be surrounded by #if UNITY_EDITOR and #endif when used in a type that is also compiled for a standalone build.

params.value: The SDK Setup to set as the loaded SDK.

methods.name: TryLoadSDKSetup(int startIndex, bool tryToReinitialize, VRTK_SDKSetup[] sdkSetups)
methods.summary: Tries to load a valid VRTK_SDKSetup from a list.
methods.remarks: The first loadable VRTK_SDKSetup in the list will be loaded. Will fall back to disable VR if none of the provided Setups is useable.

params.value: The index of the VRTK_SDKSetup to start the loading with.
Whether or not to retry initializing and using the currently set but unusable VR Device.
The list to try to load a VRTK_SDKSetup from.

methods.name: UnloadSDKSetup(bool disableVR)
methods.summary: Unloads the currently loaded VRTK_SDKSetup, if there is one.

params.value: Whether to disable VR altogether after unloading the SDK Setup.

events.name: LoadedSetupChanged
events.summary: The event invoked whenever the loaded SDK Setup changes.

properties.name: AvailableScriptingDefineSymbolPredicateInfos
properties.summary: All found scripting define symbol predicate attributes with associated method info.

properties.name: behavioursToToggleOnLoadedSetupChange
properties.summary: All behaviours that need toggling whenever loadedSetup changes.

properties.name: InstalledBoundariesSDKInfos
properties.summary: All installed boundaries SDK infos. This is a subset of AvailableBoundariesSDKInfos. It contains only those available SDK infos for which an SDK_ScriptingDefineSymbolPredicateAttribute exists that uses the same symbol and whose associated method returns true.

properties.name: InstalledControllerSDKInfos
properties.summary: All installed controller SDK infos. This is a subset of AvailableControllerSDKInfos. It contains only those available SDK infos for which an SDK_ScriptingDefineSymbolPredicateAttribute exists that uses the same symbol and whose associated method returns true.

properties.name: InstalledHeadsetSDKInfos
properties.summary: All installed headset SDK infos. This is a subset of AvailableHeadsetSDKInfos. It contains only those available SDK infos for which an SDK_ScriptingDefineSymbolPredicateAttribute exists that uses the same symbol and whose associated method returns true.

properties.name: InstalledSystemSDKInfos
properties.summary: All installed system SDK infos. This is a subset of AvailableSystemSDKInfos. It contains only those available SDK infos for which an SDK_ScriptingDefineSymbolPredicateAttribute exists that uses the same symbol and whose associated method returns true.

properties.name: instance
properties.summary: The singleton instance to access the SDK Manager variables from.

properties.name: loadedSetup
properties.summary: The loaded SDK Setup. if no setup is currently loaded.
